{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.3",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 3 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:1",
      "text": "My son, forget not my laws; but let thine heart keep my words:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:2",
      "text": "for length of existence, and years of life, and peace, shall they add to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:3",
      "text": "Let not mercy and truth forsake thee; but bind them about thy neck:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:4",
      "text": "so shalt thou find favour: and do thou provide things honest in the sight of the Lord, and of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:5",
      "text": "Trust in God with all thine heart; and be not exalted in thine own wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:6",
      "text": "In all thy ways acquaint thyself with her, that she may rightly direct thy paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:7",
      "text": "Be not wise in thine own conceit; but fear God, and depart from all evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:8",
      "text": "Then shall there be health to thy body, and good keeping to thy bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:9",
      "text": "Honour the Lord with thy just labours, and give him the first of thy fruits of righteousness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:10",
      "text": "that thy storehouses may be completely filled with corn, and that thy presses may burst forth with wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:11",
      "text": "✡My son, despise not the chastening of the Lord; nor faint when thou art rebuked of him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:12",
      "text": "for whom the Lord loves, he rebukes, and scourges every son whom he receives.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:13",
      "text": "Blessed is the man who has found wisdom, and the mortal who knows prudence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:14",
      "text": "For it is better to traffic for her, than for treasures of gold and silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:15",
      "text": "And she is more valuable than precious stones: no evil thing shall resist her: she is well known to all that approach her, and no precious thing is equal to her in value.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:16",
      "text": "For length of existence and years of life are in her right hand; and in her left hand are wealth and glory: 16a out of her mouth proceeds righteousness, and she carries law and mercy upon her tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:17",
      "text": "Her ways are good ways, and all her paths are peaceful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:18",
      "text": "She is a tree of life to all that lay hold upon her; and she is a secure help to all that stay themselves on her, as on the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:19",
      "text": "God by wisdom founded the earth, and by prudence he prepared the heavens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:20",
      "text": "By understanding were the depths broken up, and the clouds dropped water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:21",
      "text": "My son, let them not pass from thee, but keep my counsel and understanding:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:22",
      "text": "that thy soul may live, and that there may be grace round thy neck; 22a and it shall be health to thy flesh, and safety to thy bones:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:23",
      "text": "that thou mayest go confidently in peace in all thy ways, and that thy foot may not stumble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:24",
      "text": "For if thou rest, thou shalt be undismayed; and if thou sleep, thou shalt slumber sweetly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:25",
      "text": "And thou shalt not be afraid of alarm coming upon thee, neither of approaching attacks of ungodly men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:26",
      "text": "For the Lord shall be over all thy ways, and shall establish thy foot that thou be not moved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:27",
      "text": "Forbear not to do good to the poor, whensoever thy hand may have power to help him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:28",
      "text": "Say not, Come back another time, to-morrow I will give; while thou art able to do him good: for thou knowest not what the next day will bring forth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:29",
      "text": "Devise not evil against thy friend, living near thee and trusting in thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:30",
      "text": "Be not ready to quarrel with a man without a cause, lest he do thee some harm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:31",
      "text": "Procure not the reproaches of bad men, neither do thou covet their ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:32",
      "text": "For every transgressor is unclean before the Lord; neither does he sit among the righteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:33",
      "text": "The curse of God is in the houses of the ungodly; but the habitations of the just are blessed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:34",
      "text": "The Lord resists the proud; but he gives grace to the humble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.3.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:35",
      "text": "The wise shall inherit glory; but the ungodly have exalted their own dishonour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
